      "text": [
        " اَلصَّادِقُ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : \"مَنْ مَرَّ بِبَسَاتِينَ فَلاَ بَأْسَ بِأَنْ يَأْكُلَ مِنْ ثِمَارِهَا وَ لاَ يَحْمِلْ مَعَهُ مِنْهَا شَيْئاً\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3678 - Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) said:\n\"Whoever passes by orchards, there is no harm in eating from their fruits, but he should not carry anything from them with him.\""
        ]
      }
